# OpenTelemetry Auto-Instrumentation Rule

Every project must be observable. When writing code, always include OpenTelemetry instrumentation across three layers: auto-instrumentation for infrastructure, structured spans for AI pipelines, and GenAI semantic convention spans for LLM calls.

## Layer 1: Tracing Setup & Auto-Instrumentation

When creating a new project or adding tracing for the first time, set up the OTel tracer provider. The OTLP endpoint comes from the environment — never hardcode it.

```typescript
import { NodeTracerProvider } from "@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-node";
import { BatchSpanProcessor } from "@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-base";
import { OTLPTraceExporter } from "@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http";
import { resourceFromAttributes } from "@opentelemetry/resources";
import { ATTR_SERVICE_NAME } from "@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions";
import { getNodeAutoInstrumentations } from "@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node";
import { registerInstrumentations } from "@opentelemetry/instrumentation";

const resource = resourceFromAttributes({ [ATTR_SERVICE_NAME]: "my-service" });
const exporter = new OTLPTraceExporter();
const provider = new NodeTracerProvider({
  resource,
  spanProcessors: [new BatchSpanProcessor(exporter)],
});
provider.register();

registerInstrumentations({
  instrumentations: [getNodeAutoInstrumentations()],
});
```

This gives you automatic tracing for HTTP, gRPC, AWS SDK, database clients, and more — zero manual spans needed for infrastructure calls.

Dependencies to include:
- `@opentelemetry/api`
- `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-node`
- `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-base`
- `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http`
- `@opentelemetry/resources`
- `@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions`
- `@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node`
- `@opentelemetry/instrumentation`

Or use the helper: `import { setupTracing } from "cursor-auto-otel";`

## Layer 2: AI Pipeline Structure

When writing multi-step processing pipelines (data pipelines, AI pipelines, workflow orchestrations), wrap each stage in an OTel span. Use `INTERNAL` span kind for pipeline stages.

### Required attributes for pipeline spans

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `pipeline.name` | string | Name of the overall pipeline |
| `pipeline.stage` | string | Name of this specific stage |
| `pipeline.execution_type` | string | One of: `"llm"`, `"heuristic"`, `"programmatic"` |
| `pipeline.success` | boolean | Whether the stage completed without error |

### Manual instrumentation pattern

```typescript
import { trace, SpanKind, SpanStatusCode } from "@opentelemetry/api";

const tracer = trace.getTracer("my-service");

async function runPipeline(input: string) {
  return tracer.startActiveSpan("my-pipeline", { kind: SpanKind.INTERNAL }, async (pipelineSpan) => {
    pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline");
    try {
      const ctx = trace.setSpan(context.active(), pipelineSpan);

      const step1Result = await tracer.startActiveSpan("validate-input", { kind: SpanKind.INTERNAL }, ctx, async (span) => {
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.stage", "validate-input");
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.execution_type", "programmatic");
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline");
        try {
          const result = await validateInput(input);
          span.setAttribute("pipeline.success", true);
          return result;
        } catch (error) {
          span.setAttribute("pipeline.success", false);
          span.recordException(error as Error);
          span.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: (error as Error).message });
          throw error;
        } finally {
          span.end();
        }
      });

      // ... more stages ...

      pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.success", true);
      return finalResult;
    } catch (error) {
      pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.success", false);
      pipelineSpan.recordException(error as Error);
      pipelineSpan.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: (error as Error).message });
      throw error;
    } finally {
      pipelineSpan.end();
    }
  });
}
```

### Using the helper library

```typescript
import { tracePipeline, traceStep, traceLLMCall } from "cursor-auto-otel";

const result = await tracePipeline("my-pipeline", async (pipeline) => {
  const validated = await traceStep(pipeline, "validate-input", { executionType: "programmatic" }, async () => {
    return validateInput(input);
  });

  const enriched = await traceStep(pipeline, "enrich-data", { executionType: "heuristic" }, async () => {
    return applyHeuristics(validated);
  });

  return enriched;
});
```

### Execution type guidance

- `"llm"` — stage calls an LLM or generative AI model (prefer `traceLLMCall` for these)
- `"heuristic"` — stage applies rules, scoring, regex, or other deterministic-but-configurable logic
- `"programmatic"` — stage is pure code: validation, transformation, DB lookups, API calls

## Layer 3: GenAI LLM Call Spans

When writing code that calls LLM APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Bedrock, etc.), create spans following the OTel GenAI semantic conventions. Use `CLIENT` span kind — these are outbound calls to an external AI service.

### Span naming

Span name MUST follow the format: `{gen_ai.operation.name} {gen_ai.request.model}`

Examples: `"chat gpt-4o"`, `"chat claude-sonnet-4-20250514"`, `"embeddings text-embedding-3-small"`

### Required and recommended attributes

| Attribute | Requirement | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `gen_ai.operation.name` | Required | `"chat"`, `"text_completion"`, `"embeddings"` |
| `gen_ai.provider.name` | Required | `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"aws.bedrock"` |
| `gen_ai.request.model` | Required (if available) | `"gpt-4o"`, `"claude-sonnet-4-20250514"` |
| `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` | Recommended | `150` |
| `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens` | Recommended | `230` |
| `gen_ai.response.finish_reasons` | Recommended | `["stop"]` |
| `gen_ai.request.max_tokens` | Recommended | `1024` |
| `gen_ai.response.model` | Recommended | `"gpt-4o-2024-08-06"` |
| `gen_ai.response.id` | Recommended | `"chatcmpl-abc123"` |
| `gen_ai.request.temperature` | Recommended | `0.7` |

### Well-known provider names

Use these exact strings for `gen_ai.provider.name`: `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"aws.bedrock"`, `"azure.ai.openai"`, `"cohere"`, `"deepseek"`, `"gcp.gemini"`, `"gcp.vertex_ai"`, `"groq"`, `"mistral_ai"`, `"perplexity"`

### Well-known operation names

`"chat"`, `"text_completion"`, `"embeddings"`, `"create_agent"`, `"invoke_agent"`, `"execute_tool"`, `"generate_content"`

### Manual instrumentation pattern

```typescript
import { trace, SpanKind, SpanStatusCode } from "@opentelemetry/api";

const tracer = trace.getTracer("my-service");

async function callLLM(messages: Array<{ role: string; content: string }>) {
  const model = "gpt-4o";
  return tracer.startActiveSpan(`chat ${model}`, { kind: SpanKind.CLIENT }, async (span) => {
    span.setAttribute("gen_ai.operation.name", "chat");
    span.setAttribute("gen_ai.provider.name", "openai");
    span.setAttribute("gen_ai.request.model", model);
    span.setAttribute("gen_ai.request.max_tokens", 1024);

    try {
      const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({
        model,
        messages,
        max_tokens: 1024,
      });

      span.setAttribute("gen_ai.usage.input_tokens", response.usage?.prompt_tokens ?? 0);
      span.setAttribute("gen_ai.usage.output_tokens", response.usage?.completion_tokens ?? 0);
      span.setAttribute("gen_ai.response.finish_reasons", [response.choices[0]?.finish_reason ?? "unknown"]);
      span.setAttribute("gen_ai.response.model", response.model);
      span.setAttribute("gen_ai.response.id", response.id);

      return response.choices[0]?.message?.content ?? "";
    } catch (error) {
      span.recordException(error as Error);
      span.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: (error as Error).message });
      throw error;
    } finally {
      span.end();
    }
  });
}
```

### Using the helper library

```typescript
import { traceLLMCall } from "cursor-auto-otel";

const reply = await traceLLMCall(
  pipeline,
  "generate-response",
  { provider: "openai", model: "gpt-4o", operationName: "chat", maxTokens: 1024 },
  async (captureUsage) => {
    const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({
      model: "gpt-4o",
      messages,
      max_tokens: 1024,
    });

    captureUsage(
      response.usage?.prompt_tokens ?? 0,
      response.usage?.completion_tokens ?? 0,
      response.choices[0]?.finish_reason,
    );

    return response.choices[0]?.message?.content ?? "";
  },
);
```

### Anthropic example

```typescript
const reply = await traceLLMCall(
  pipeline,
  "analyze-document",
  { provider: "anthropic", model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514", operationName: "chat", maxTokens: 2048 },
  async (captureUsage) => {
    const response = await anthropic.messages.create({
      model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
      max_tokens: 2048,
      messages,
    });

    captureUsage(
      response.usage.input_tokens,
      response.usage.output_tokens,
      response.stop_reason ?? undefined,
    );

    return response.content[0].type === "text" ? response.content[0].text : "";
  },
);
```

## Error Handling Rules

1. Always call `span.recordException(error)` when catching errors
2. Always call `span.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message })` on failure
3. Always call `span.end()` in a `finally` block — never skip it
4. Set `pipeline.success` to `false` on the span when a stage fails
5. Let errors propagate — don't swallow exceptions just to end spans cleanly

## Span Kind Rules

| Context | Span Kind |
|---|---|
| LLM API call (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) | `CLIENT` |
| External HTTP/gRPC call | `CLIENT` |
| Pipeline root span | `INTERNAL` |
| Pipeline stage | `INTERNAL` |
| Incoming HTTP request (server) | `SERVER` |

## Checklist

When writing any new code, verify:

- [ ] Tracing is set up (tracer provider + OTLP exporter configured)
- [ ] Multi-step pipelines have a root span and child spans per stage
- [ ] Each pipeline stage span has `pipeline.stage`, `pipeline.execution_type`, and `pipeline.success`
- [ ] LLM calls have `gen_ai.operation.name`, `gen_ai.provider.name`, and `gen_ai.request.model`
- [ ] Token usage (`gen_ai.usage.input_tokens`, `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens`) is captured after LLM responses
- [ ] Errors are recorded on spans with `recordException` and `ERROR` status
- [ ] All spans are ended in `finally` blocks
- [ ] No OTLP endpoints are hardcoded — use `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` env var
